(39, 'One for the Rajma Chawal Lovers!', 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'AUGUST 05,2017', '<p>\nRajma Chawal is the dish no Indian can say no to. It has always been everyone''s favourite. There are some who can eat Rajma Chawal in all three meals. So this one''s dedicated to all you bhukkads, screw lean gotta love the bean. \n</p>\n\n         <p>\n\nHere are the things you can relate to if Rajma Chawal is the love of your life:\n</p>\n\n<p>\n1. When in the worst mood ever, life sucks & it gets difficult to take a single step forward. Dragging yourself you ask you mom ''Khane mein kya hai?'' & your ears get the golden words ''Rajma chawal''. Who''s up & kicking, oh that''s you.\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/rajma1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\n2. Your mother knows the way to your heart is with garma garam Rajma Chawal & expect the obvious bombardment of questions ''Koi pata rakhi/rakha hai kya, shaadi krle''\n</p>\n\n<p>\n3. There are days when you went to a fancy restaurant, but all your heart really wanted is Rajma Chawal.What a drag.\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/rajma2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\n4. That disappointing moment when you take a huge serving of Rajma Chawal in someone else''s home . ''Will it be enough for rest, screw it, let just no one see my plate, gulp gulp''.\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/rajma3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\n5. When your mother is trying to convince you for a rishta & hit you with her best stroke i.e. rajma chawal.\n</p>\n<p>\n6. When you know there is Rajma Chawal for dinner at home &you skip meals so that you can pounce on the plate like a hungry tiger.\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/rajma4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\n7. When your parents are screaming at you about something, but all you can think is ''tomorrow''s a good day for rajma chawal'' \n</p>\n\n<p>\n8. You know your stomach''s gonna burst after the amount you served. ''Don''t judge me people, this could be my last meal''. Cut the drama, just eat.\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/rajma5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\n9. How you visit all shaadis & curse that there is only ''chole'' like why won''t you make rajma bro!\n</p>\n\n<p>\n10. Your ultimate goal in life is to marry the person who looks at you the way you look at Rajma Chawal.''I was searching you throughout my life''.\n</p> \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/rajma6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>', 'The Editor', 'rajma.png', 'rajmarec.jpg'),
(41, 'Top 5 Healthiest Foods in the World!', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'JULY 25,2017', '<p ><center><i>Now get fit, without even having to give up eating!!!</center></i>\n</p>\n\n<p>\nWell one thing is eating &amp one is eating smart. Which one do you choose? Here are the food items that you should definitely include in your everyday meals!\n</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">Lemons</h2> \n<p>\n\n<b>How to consume them?</b></p>\n\n<p>Lemons can add an amazing flavor to a couple of things, rice for instance can be cooked very well with lemon. Alternatively, you can add it to your green tea or have it \nwith a mix of hot water and honey.</p>\n<p><b>Why Lemon?</b></p>\n<p>One lemon a day fulfills a person&#39;s 100 percent vitamin C needs. It has been speculated that they can prevent cancer by slowing the growth of certain cells. They''re also widely \nknown for their anti-oxidant properties.\n</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hd5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                  \n<h2 class="section-heading">Broccoli</h2>\n<p>\n\n<b>How to consume it?</b></p>\n\n<p>\nIt definitely isn''t a favorite food item, especially among children. Some interesting ways to include it in your meals are to cook it with rice, mixed vegetables or even as a pizza topping!</p>\n<p><b>\nWhy Broccoli?</b></p>\n<p>It is rich in Vitamin K, B1, B2, B6, B9, Amino Acid, Sodium, Potassium and is known to have more Vitamin E than olive oil. Basically it''s really healthy!</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hd1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                   \n<h2 class="section-heading">Dark Chocolate</h2>\n \n<p><b>How to consume it?</b></p>\n<p>Well, unwrap the bar and eat it! But be careful not to eat too much at a time. Have a cube with a glass of milk. Use it to sweeten or flavor the milk.</p>\n<p><b>Why Dark Chocolate?</b></p>\n<p>It is a lesser known fact that dark chocolate is good for your heart. It is rich in antioxidants and flavonoids. It also helps in keeping a check on the blood pressure & stubborn cholesterol.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hd4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                   \n<h2 class="section-heading">Potato (Surprise! Surprise!)\n\n</h2>\n \n<p>\n\n<b>How to consume them?</b></p>\n<p>\nWell, obviously not as chips from the packet. In fact potatoes in any packaged form will not bring you any benefits. Boiled potatoes in salads, or as hash browns or even as fries are the way to go!</p>\n<p>Baked potatoes taste good too!\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Why Potatoes?</b></p> \n<p>\nPotatoes contain cell building folates, fight cancerous cells and help in making the immune system strong! </p>\n<p>They also contain good carbs!\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hd2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                   \n<h2 class="section-heading">Walnuts</h2>  \n<p>\n<b>How to consume them?</b></p>\n<p>Eat it as it is. Garnish your oats with walnuts, bake them with cakes and bread or soak them in milk!</p>\n<p><b>Why walnuts?</b></p>\n\n<p>They contain Omega-3 Fatty Acids which are known to assist in maintaining cholesterol levels.\nThey may even prevent us from damage against the sun!</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hd6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n', 'Artika Singh', 'healthy.png', 'healthyrec.jpg'),
(45, 'Nuts about Coconut Oil Yet?', 'BEAUTY & WELLNESS', 'August 24,2017', '<p><b>If flared pants and polka dots can make a comeback, then why leave vintage health and beauty trends!</b></p>\n<p>Our moms and grand moms have probably been trying hard to make us see the multiple benefits of <b>coconut oil</b> for years. But obviously we are quicker at noticing something we read in a magazine or hear online than paying attention to them! I, following their footsteps, will once again try to prove that coconut oil is indeed the <b>BEST</b>. And this is truly, completely & wholly based on my personal experience.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/coconut1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n\n  \n<h2 class="section-heading">\n1.	Magic Potion for skin and hair!!!</h2>\n\n<p>\n\nTraditionally coconut oil is known to be an <b>excellent moisturizer </b>coupled with that it''s anti-oxidant properties makes it the perfect remedy for not only dry and flaky skin but also degenerative skin problems like dermatitis, eczema, premature ageing, psoriasis and other such infections. So get some coconut oil massage everyday & save yourself from paying those hefty bills at a dermatologist''s clinic.\n\nAnd ladies and gentlemen trying <b>to fight hair loss and hair damage</b>, have you tried this yet? Coconut oil prevents your hair from losing healthy proteins thereby giving you healthy, shiny and strong and lice free hair.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/coconut2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n\n\n \n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n2.	Want whiter underarms?</h2>\n\n\n<p>\nCoconut Oil is the answer! I actually learnt about this from my dermatologist when I went in for <b>underarms lightening</b> procedure. She asked me to avoid the procedure and try this home remedy instead. And it worked!! Our underarm skin & inner side of upper thighs tend to get discolored as it is subjected continuously to friction. Fix this by applying coconut oil on the affected areas, two times in a day! Yes, it''s really that simple!\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/coconut3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n           \n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n3.	Way to a healthier heart</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Contrary to popular belief, coconut oil, unlike other saturated fat sources, is <b>beneficial for the human heart.</b> It is known to contain 50 percent Lauric acid, which helps in preventing both high cholesterol and blood pressure. Consuming coconut oil keeps the arteries healthy and lowers the chances of heart diseases.\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/coconut4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n             \n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n4.	Weight Loss</h2>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Yes you heard it right! Ok let''s bring down that excitement by just a notch. You still need to exercise but including coconut oil in your diet will definitely <b>increase the rate of weight loss.</b> Scientifically, coconut oil contains short and medium length fatty acid chains which can be broken down more easily. In lay man''s term, it''s easier to digest! With regulation of metabolism it further adds to the weight loss. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/coconut5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                 \n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n5.	A Shining Smile Please!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n<p>Coconut oil facilitates the absorption of calcium, major component of our teeth, in our body! Coconut oil thus helps in maintaining stronger, <b>healthier and whiter teeth,</b> avoiding root infections and most of all, saving us from the horror of visiting the dentist!\n</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/coconut6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    ', 'Artika Singh', 'coconut.png', 'coconutrec.jpg'),
(46, 'I have got specs appeal!', 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'August 25 , 2017', '<p>\nSitting in the hall, watching my favourite cartoons with my brother on any usual evening. My mom passed & jumped saying why are you scrunching your eyes. I was like ''I am not'', of course not wanting to go for an eye check up. But mom''s the god, no excuses works ever.\n</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	<p>\nSo I went for the check up & came back with spectacles. Hence started my journey with my buddy, my specs, at the age of 12 and they have not left my side since. Of course the pairs have changed over the years but the feelings haven''t.\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n\n\n\n\n       \n\n<p>\nSome feel it''s a pain but for me they have become a habit & not a bad one. So let''s count all the good things that happened to me after I got my first pair.\n</p>\n\n<ul><li>\nMy nose bridge, where specs rest, became more prominent. Trust me it was non-existent,haha\n</li>\n\n<li>\n\nIt made me look more studious & responsible so I was always an option for the monitor or house captain, thanks to my above average marks as well.</li>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n\n\n\n\n\n<li>I got to change my look with every new frame.</li>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n\n\n\n<li>No watery eyes cause of dust or smoke.</li>\n\n<li>You get noticed easily in a crowd of non-specky people.\n</li>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n\n<li>People listen to you with more attention cause your specs reflect seriousness & focussed approach.</li>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n\n<li>People find you cuter especially when you adjust your frame or scrunch your nose.\n</li>\n\n\n\n\n\n<li>\nAnd of course you take your specs off and you are a new personality.</li>\n\n\n                   \n\n</ul>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/specs7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\n\nImagine you are going on a date and generally the specky you take a break and opt for lens, dress up nicely with beautiful eye makeup and your ever serious personality turns into this charming & uber cute one. People can''t take their eyes off of you. \n</p>\n\n<p>\nAlso you have so many varieties, so many colours, so many shapes when it comes to specs. Going to an optical store brings out the child in me who is excited to see what''s in store for me this time.\n\n</p>\n\n<p>\nOf course there are few limitations like when it rains, when you want to go swimming or when you want to put sun glasses but I guess minor hiccups are not something which will make me give up my childhood buddies after all we are partners for life.\n\n</p>\n', 'Chetna Dhull', 'specs.png', 'specsrec.jpg'),
(54, 'The Age of Home Workout!!!', 'Beauty & wellness', 'August 17,2017', '\n<p><center>With hours spent working, consuming maximum portion of your day; we understand there is no time to hit the gym.</center></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Only a healthy body and mind combined can enable us to work hard and achieve our goals. Despite that, most of us do not pay any heed to fitness. Well we don''t blame you. We believe when you say there is no time. With endless office hours, never ending traffic, the persistent red signals never going green, household chores & what not. So ultimately you can''t go to gym but the gym can definitely come to you.  Here are the best videos on the internet that can guide you through a home workout session! Who needs a gym? Roll down the bed & let''s start.</p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">The Four-Minute Wonder!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/work1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Just 4 minutes every day, sounds like a good deal right?</p>\n\n<p>Yup a 4 minute work out to replace that one hour of gym. With simple but effective exercises\nlike squats, push ups, mountain climber , lunges &amp; jumping jacks this workout will surely make\nyou feel energized &amp; pumped but not exhausted.</p>\n\n<p><i>Where:</i><a href="https://youtu.be/FRDGlIJTVt8"> https://youtu.be/FRDGlIJTVt8</a></p>\n<p><i>Channel:</i> Bright Side</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">No harm dancing on your own!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/work2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>For those who want to dance their way to fitness!!</p>\n\n<p>A 40 minutes dance cardio to burn fat. Chuck the gym and aerobics. Just tune in to this video &amp;\nstart dancing to lose those extra pounds. It doesn''t feel like you are exercising, it''s super fun.\nAre you ready to learn the dance cardio routine?</p>\n\n<p><i>Where:</i><a href=" https://youtu.be/ijNdZZ4hgw4"> https://youtu.be/ijNdZZ4hgw4</a></p>\n<p><i>Channel:</i> Rachella Nisson</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nA Little Zumba Doesn''t Hurt Nobody!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/work3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>	Zumba is the new running!</p>\n\n<p>One of the best warm-ups I have experienced. With the awesome beats playing, your body just\nmoves on its own. Get up and kicking &amp; dance your way to fitness.</p>\n<p><i>Where:</i><a href="https://youtu.be/xfmHPW-AfQs"> https://youtu.be/xfmHPW-AfQs</a></p>\n<p><i>Channel:</i> Vijaya Tupurani </p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n\nNo Equipment Needed!\n</h2>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/work4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Just 10-minutes for a healthier day!</p>\n\n<p>Just 10 minutes HIIT (High Intensity Interval Training) workout, no equipment required. You\nwill find loads of home workout but this is where you stop . Get ready for some intense work\nout that''ll make you sweat all the fat.</p>\n<p><i>Where:</i><a href="https://youtu.be/DZ6voLaG9_I"> https://youtu.be/DZ6voLaG9_I</a></p>\n<p><i>Channel:</i> StayFitandTravel </p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nBollywood Workout!\n</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/work5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>               \n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>From Bollywood, to your homes!</p>\n\n<p>Listen to the music, and follow the diva Bipasha Basu for a 30 minutes aerobics dance workout.\nFeel the stretch, warm up the body &amp; break free. You''ll be drenched but not tired and obviously\nend up wanting some more.</p>\n\n<p><i>Where:</i><a href="https://youtu.be/tj9d6aBOzDo"> https://youtu.be/tj9d6aBOzDo</a></p>\n<p><i>Channel:</i> Good Health 24/7</p>\n\n<p>\nSo procrastinate no more. You owe it to all the clothes that you bought with such excitement but don''t fit anymore. You owe it to your body for all the sedentary sitting in the office. But most importantly you owe it to yourself. Stay fit, stay healthy.</p>\n\n', 'Artika Singh', 'workout.png', 'workoutrec.jpg'),
(47, 'How to Style a Maxi Dress in 4 ways', 'FASHION', 'August 25 , 2017', '<p>Hey you lovely people!</p>\n<p>Maxi dresses, as we all know, are not only one of the most flattering, comfortable and forgiving items of clothing to wear, but they''re also surprisingly versatile. They''re easy to add layers over as well as hide layers under, making them the perfect transitional pieces of clothing.</p>\n<p>So recently when I picked up this black Maxi dress from ZARA, I realised that I could actually wear it to a lot of occasions. From dressed up fancy to boho chic, work appropriate to a playful weekend ensemble, this basic outfit could be styled in numerous ways and thus, I decided to create these 4 looks and share them with you all.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">1) The College Look</h2>\n<br>\n<p>This casual ensemble is definitely my favourite. Whether you are going to college or simply hanging out with friends, this outfit can never let you down.</p>\n<p>Just throw a denim/bomber jacket over your maxi dress and complete the look with a cute bag and accessories. You can even knot the bottom of your dress for a street-chic appeal.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                   \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n\n \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Outfit- Maxi dress & Denim jacket: Zara, Shoes: H&M, Sunglasses: Rayban, Bag: River Island)\n</span>\n  \n\n<h2 class="section-heading">2) Holiday Look</h2>\n \n<p>A maxi dress is the perfect choice when we talk of holidays and beach destinations. Its breezy silhouette brings an ethereal vibe which is beautiful for the summer months.</p>\n<p>Dress up your maxi with minimal accessories and a floppy hat/fedora. You can pair it with flip flops, ankle-tie flats or leather strap sandals.</p>\n\n\n\n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                       \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi8.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Outfit: Bag-Zara, Flatforms-Zara, Hat- Spain)\n</span>\n  \n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">3) Dinner Date Look</h2><br>\n<p>Whether its a black-tie event or a dinner date, just give your look a lift (literally) with heels and some statement accessories. Its amazing how a simple Maxi dress can be transitioned into a glamorous night outfit with minor additions.</p>\n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi9.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi10.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi11.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n\n\n\n\n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi12.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi13.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Outfit: Bag-Topshop, Belt-H&M, Shoes-River Island, Neckpiece- eBay.co.uk, Watch- Tissot)\n</span>\n  \n\n<h2 class="section-heading">4) Work Look</h2><br>\n<p>Wearing a maxi dress to work can be a bit tricky. The key is to select options that''ll work well as a canvas for various accessories to add polished, professional elements to the look.</p>\n<p>For instance, add a longline blazer and a structured bag with minimal jewellery and nude pumps for a modern spin, like in the pictures below.</p>\n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi14.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi15.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi16.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi17.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/maxi18.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Outfit: Blazer-Vero Moda, Bag- Louis Vuitton, Pearl neckpiece- Hyderabad, Glasses-Pierre Cardin)\n</span>\n  \n\n<p>There''s a reason why maxi dresses are a favourite summer staple-they''re universally befitting, cool (in more ways than one!) and ridiculously comfortable. I''d say that''s winning in the most fashionable sense.   </p>\n<p>Much Love </p> \n<p>Ciao!</p>', 'Naina Ruhail', 'maxi.png', 'maxirec.jpg'),
(74, 'You didn''t see it coming!', 'Entertainment', 'September 21,2017', '\r\n<p> "Let me grow up & I will kick his ass", that''s what you tell yourself when you get bullied by an older boy being a kid. And suddenly your wish come true and boom there''s puberty, straight in your face. With no prior experience & of course staying with a family, it becomes a daunting task to handle your uninvited friend</p>\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> Your little buddy gets a mind of his own</h2><p>\r\nThere you are cozying in your sofa watching your favourite songs or reading and your buddy goes commando. And on top of that your mom asks to go out & run some errands. You try your best to convince him but he being he makes a scene out of it. Arrghhhh.</p>\r\n\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty1.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> Your voice goes from baby Groot to Thor</h2><p>\r\nGone are the days when your squeaky voice was unheard, you suddenly become the man of the house. Who''s the boss now look to your siblings, yeah!</p>\r\n\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty2.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> Your video games miss you</h2><p>\r\nYou no more think of what new game is launched. With bodily changes, your mind seeks answers & comes porn to the rescue. ''Curse you puberty'' , courtesy ''broken heart'' video games.</p>\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty3.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> Welcome moustache\r\n\r\n</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>With new facial hairs & the new look, there begins the dreams of getting it full grown up & groom it to your liking. Thoughts about which hero I want to copy. Awesome!</p>\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty4.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> Group studies become important\r\n</h2>\r\n<p>So each group invents his own ''go to guy'' for survival, whose parents generally come home late. The so called group studies to come out entertained & enlightened. ''Isi baat par kash de yaar''</p>\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty5.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> The new bullies</h2>\r\n<p>Someone else replicates your thoughts of ''bada hokar dekh lunga isse''.</p>\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty6.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> Oh!who''s that chick</h2>\r\n<p>The girls around become hotter all of a sudden. The day dreaming begins. ''Ye bhaabhi hai tum logo ki'' to friends. Like literally having erections just by hearing boobs.</p>\r\n\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty7.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> From shorts to track suit bottoms & pants</h2><p>\r\n''I am a big guy, no more shorts mom please''.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> From being loud to self-conscious</h2>\r\n<p>Gone is the kid who ran shouting across the house, you become more self-conscious after all there is an image to maintain.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2 class="section-heading"> My life my guitar</h2>\r\n<p>There begins the search for your inner talent. ''Guitar seekh leta hu, its cool''. All those endless nights thinking what new you want to explore. A singer?dancer?footballer?may be basketballer ''chalo height badhate hai''.</p>\r\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/puberty8.jpg" alt="">\r\n                    </div>\r\n\r\n<p>Well puberty sure brings a large deal of weirdness but once you get over the initial phase, expect only smooth sailing ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n', 'Chetna Dhull', 'puberty.jpg', 'pubertyrec.jpg'),
(49, 'Dress Over Pants', 'FASHION', 'August 26,2017', '<p>Holla,</p>\n<p>Have you tried the Dress-Over-Pants trend yet? </p>\n<p>Although its one of the oldest, it has the power to revamp any wardrobe. Largely seen on and off the runway this year, this chic trend is here to stay and is definitely easy to pull off. </p>\n<p>Its a great way of updating your closet and adding life to your tired staples.  </p>\n<p>The best way to master the dress-over-pants look is by paying attention to proportions and not making it too complicated. Here are a few quick tips on how you can rock this uber cool trend: </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Talking about pants, go for neutral colors like black, white, navy or gray. Even denims look great when worn with dresses.</li>\n<li>When it comes to dress size, make sure its neither too long or short. A knee to midi length hem is perfect. Maxi dresses with high slits do work as they create a flow effect.</li>\n<li>Slim-cut trousers, cigarette pants, cropped denims and jeggings suit this style the most. If you like the slouchy or casual look, opt for flared pants.</li>\n<li>You can even wear matching pieces that are of similar color, pattern, texture or fabric.</li>\n<li>Unless you are very tall, its best to carry this look with mid to high heels to avoid looking bulky.</li>\n<li>Play with solid colors and don''t forget to accessorize.</li>\n<li>During winters, you can go for sweater dresses or leather pants. Layer up your outfit with blazers, overcoats, cropped sweats, or knits.</li>\n</ul> \n<p>I have created two different looks here to show you all this supremely chic trend. Have a look and let me know if you like it.  </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/dress1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted"></span>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/dress7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Outfit: Dress-Zara, Denims- Vero Moda, Scarf-Emilio Pucci, Sunglasses-MK, Shoes-Steve Madden)\n</span>\n<br>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/dress8.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Outfit: Dress & Pants-Zara, Clutch-Bangkok)</span>\n\n\n \n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/dress9.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted"></span>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/dress10.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted">(Septum ring- Tribe by Amprapali)\n</span>\n\n\n<p>Dos and Don''ts</p>\n<p>\n1.	Avoid wearing dresses with heavy bottoms or drapes.<br>\n2.	Keep the pants simple and experiment with dresses instead.<br>\n3.	Stick to heels and avoid wearing flats.<br>\n4.	Wear what suits your frame.<br>\n </p>\n<p>Hope you all enjoyed reading this one. If you have any queries, leave me a comment below!  </p>\n \n<p>Much Love</p>  \n<p>Ciao!</p>', 'Naina Ruhail', 'dress.png', 'dressrec.jpg'),
(48, 'It''s a bird? It''s a plane?', 'ADVENTURE', 'August 26,2017', '<p>Many of you must have heard or even done Paragliding in the breath taking Solang Valley, Bir Billing or Manali. Enjoying the mesmerizing views from a height of nearly 2000m is surely one hell of an experience. We''ve all wanted to scout the skylines like birds sometime in our lives & feel free without any bounds.  But to travel that long for those few minutes of joy, sure is difficult in today''s busy times. What? You want same in NCR. Well your wish has just been granted.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/para2.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n\n\n\n<p>Flyboy Air Safari has gone one step ahead of all the conventional adventure activities. They bring Motorized Paragliding in Gurugram to explore the clear blue skies faster than you ever have. Enjoy the absolutely stunning view of the lush green grasslands around the suburbs. Experience an exciting Paramotor Flight trip - which is a powered paraglide that operates with the help of an attached motor, harness and a propeller. </p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/para3.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n\n\n<p>And don''t worry about your safety as they''ve got you covered under the expertise of trained pilots who assure you a fun-packed aerial time. They''ve left you the option to choose the duration of your flight. </p>\n<p>Kitty Hawk (approx. distance covered: 6 - 8km)</p>\n<p>Fly yourself (approx. distance covered: 12 - 15km) </p>\n<p>Explorer (approx. distance 20-24km). </p>\n<p>You don''t need to carry much things along except a set of comfortable clothing considering you''ll be airborne, a pair of comfortable shoes, a pair of sunglasses and of course, a camera to capture the most enthralling moments  that you''re going to live in the air. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/para1.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n\n<p>So, head on to Flyboy Air Safari and live your dream, spread your wings & shout out at the top of your voice. </p>\n<p>Location | Flyboy Aero Park, Near The Ireo Grand Arch, Golf Course Extension Road, Sector 58, Gurgaon, Haryana-122102</p>\n<p>Phone | +91-9871510510</p>\n<p>Visit their website | <a href="http://www.flyboy.in/"> www.flyboy.in</a></p>\n', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'para.png', 'pararec.jpg'),
(50, 'Simply can''t resist!', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'August 26,2017', '<p>Delhites and Momos have an eternal bond, hard to put in words. It''s a feeling that all of us share mutually, say ''yeah'' who agrees, lil louder please! Merely hearing Momos, we lose it and rush towards this scrummy, not-so-messy and high on taste dish! </p>\n\n<p>Gone are the days when we had only 2 varieties to choose from. With tandoori, gravy, Afghani, kurkure and what not, the joints in the city have certainly upped their momos game and have put into perspective a whole new dimension to this delicacy. Momos like chilli paneer, butter masala, achaari and lots more are up for grabs and we''re going to tell exactly where you need to head to enjoy some insanely delicious varieties. </p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n1.	Giri Momos</h2><br>\n\n<p>With a whooping - digest this - almost 80 varieties of momos, they can certainly be called the pioneers in the domain and will never fail to delight us! With a variety of stuffings going from veg to paneer to chicken to mutton and different avatars like manchurian, gravy and tandoori, to name a few, you have got to visit them! </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/momos3.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                  \n\n\n\n<p>Location: Rajasthali Market, Main Road & ND Market, Pitampura</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n2.	Chalte Firte Momos</h2><br>\n\n<p>Gravy Momos anyone? Satisfy all your cravings here. Chalte Firte momos has the best answers to all your gravy cravings. With over 80 varieties of momos, from Akkha Paneer to Soya Tandoori, they have some offbeat momos that you momo lovers need to gobble up! </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/momos4.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                  \n\n\n<p>Locations: Kamla Nagar, Rohini, Prashant Vihar & Laxmi Nagar</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n3.	Kingdom of Momos</h2><br>\n\n<p>This place lies in the not-so-famous sabzi mandi of Janakpuri and they take their momos very seriously. Serving over 40+ varieties, this place is a paradise for all momo lovers. From Veg Pizza to Chilly Chicken to pure paneer, they''ve got it all. So what''s the hold up? </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/momos1.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                  \n\n\n\n<p>Location: 13/9 B Block, Choti Sabzi Mandi, Janakpuri</p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n4. Momo''s Cafe</h2><br>\n\n<p>With over 65 varieties of momos, this place is going to give you the glimpse of Mughalai Zaika with their momos. Order up some Kurkure or Bhatti momos or everyone''s beloved Tandoori Momos, you definitely need to visit this place for scrumptious momos! So gather your gang and drop by soon! </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/momos2.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                  \n\n\n<p>Location: A-2 Block, DDA Commercial Complex, Near Post Office, Paschim Vihar</p>\n\n<br>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for momo lovers? Visit these stupendous momo joints to taste the best momos in the city.</p>', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'momos.png', 'momosrec.jpg'),
(53, 'Keep Off from These, Till the Monsoon Lasts!', 'BEAUTY & WELLNESS', 'August 9,2017', '<p><i>Rain can incite many feelings & emotions in us, one of them is hunger!</i></p>\n\n<p>For so many of us rain is synonymous with food items like maggi, vegetable fritters, momos, to name a few. What we forget is that such things harbor harmful germs and bacteria that thrive during the monsoon. </p>\n\n\n<p>Here is a list of things you should positively avoid during rainy season!</p>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nFresh Juice - From roadside vendors</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/monsoon1.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>While fresh juice is very nutritious apart from being extremely tasty, the one procured from roadside vendors could cause problems for you. During rainy season water is easily contaminated and the same water may be used by these vendors to wash utensils, mix in juices and what not. And once you''ve consumed such water there can be a bevy of diseases waiting for you.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nLeafy Vegetables</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/monsoon2.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n\n\n<p>At least till the rains last, no one will force you to eat green leafy vegetables that you anyway dislike so much! No, we aren''t saying that leafy vegetables aren''t perfectly healthy but they''re just not the right choice for rainy season. The rationale behind this is that the moisture content in these vegetables puts them at risk of being contaminated by the same bacteria that dwell in stagnant water. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\nFried Food</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/monsoon3.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n\n\n<p>You''ll probably curse us for this one. I mean when do we expect you to eat pakoras and samosas, if not in the rain? Well, it is a scientifically proven fact that the human digestive system takes longer to digest food during monsoons. At such a time, eating fried food is equivalent to burdening your stomach.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\nSea Food</h2>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/monsoon4.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Monsoon or no monsoon, only a few places in Delhi can be trusted when it comes to serving, clean, hygienic and well prepared sea food. Since the breeding season of fish coincides with the monsoon, it is not a wise thing to consume sea food.</p>\n\n<p>So eat healthy & enjoy the rainy season to the fullest. Wash everything well before consuming. Stick to fruits, pulses, rice & lighter oils like olive oil or sunflower oil for good maintenance of your digestive system. </p>', 'Artika Singh', 'monsoon.png', 'monsoonrec.jpg'),
(52, 'Tea: Our Life Saviour', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'August 27,2017', '<p>''Tea is the elixir of life'' the insightful words quoted by Lao Tzu gives everyone no option other than to nod their head in agreement. Our day begins with a sip of tea and it is a good reason to possess a relaxed, refreshed and an activated mind. One can only wish for late nights, good books, warm tea & nice dreams. If these things are in our possession there is no need for any other serene feeling in this world. The tender aroma hitting one''s nostrils on a rainy day makes us disappear into a world of quiet contemplation of life. Such is the part tea holds in our life. Below are some of the popular varieties once should try in their lifetime.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n\n1.	Black Tea or Red Tea </h2>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/tea1.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n<p>\nWhen strongly blended tea leaves are added to boiling water, a reddish mixture is formed which is meant to be filtered. Its aroma is quite natural and soothing & helps boost your metabolism, but refrain taking on an empty stomach.\n\n</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n2.	Oolong Tea</h2>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/tea2.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n\n<p>This traditional Chinese tea requires special preparation method. Generally, 3 grams of tea per 200 ml of water, or about two teaspoons of oolong tea per cup, should be used. The water should not be exactly boiling, 93 to 96 &#176;C water is enough and steeped 3-10 minutes. It is used to sharpen thinking skills and improve mental alertness. </p>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n3.	Pu-Erh Tea</h2>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/tea3.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n\n<p>Generally, pu-erh is rinsed frequently to remove the dust caused due to aging. Steeping is done for a longer time to extract its flavour but if overdone, there is a chance you might kill the taste. Some call it miracle weight loss tea. Also aids in digestion & reduction of cholesterol.</p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n4.	Green Tea</h2>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/tea4.png" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                   \n                    \n\n\n<p>Craving for a healthy and a beautiful body? Then you must make the habit of drinking green tea. The water shouldn''t be excessively hot because it might cause a bitter taste. For better results try drinking it with honey rather than sugar.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nBenefits of Tea:</h2><br>\n\n<p>Benefits of consuming tea go far beyond refreshment. Below are some of the benefits one can avail from just a cup of tea regularly.</p>\n<p>\n1.	Consumption of green tea can possibly help to stave off cancer<br>\n2.	The antioxidants present in tea help our body to regenerate & repair<br>\n3.	A cup of tea daily reduces the possibility of a heart stroke<br>\n4.	Research proves that Green Tea prevents bone loss<br>\n5.	It boosts the immune system and prevents cavities in mouth helping with a bright smile in its course<br>\n6.	Tea that is unadulterated is calorie free and has fewer amounts of caffeine<br>\n7.	Tea helps keep you hydrated<br>\n8.	It helps you stay calmer & at the same time more alert<br>\n9.	Our digestion is boosted<br>\n10.	Tea can help bad breath<br>\n</p>\n<p>So don''t forget to have your daily chai ki chuski!</p>\n', 'Geeta Sowmya', 'tea.png', 'tearec.jpg');
