(55, 'Is there a smart way to eat healthy?', 'Beauty & wellness', 'August 17,2017', '<p> <center> Here''s a question to all those diet chart followers, \nare you really eating smartly?</center></p>\n\n\n\n<p>I understand most of you are boggled at what can be an un-smart way to eat healthy?\n</p>\n\n\n\n\n<p>When it comes to eating healthy, most of our gyaan come from online sources and accordingly the foods suggested are also not regional. Like how on earth will I find pork chops, ground beef, artichokes, greek yogurt, tuna etc on my baju wala baniya. Never having consulted a professional nutritionist I would''ve continued blaming non-availability of things for my not so internationally perfect eating habits if it wasn''t for a video, that admittedly, I only watched because I thought that Alia Bhatt was wearing a really cute top. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/eat1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>Recently, while watching a Facebook live session hosted by celebrity nutritionist and author, <i>Rujuta Diwekar</i> and Bollywood''s best, <i>Alia Bhatt</i>, it all became a little clearer to me. Rujuta Diwekar, emphasized on the concept of eating "locally", which she says is the right way to eat healthy. Let me elucidate the concept of "eating locally" using a few examples.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/eat2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n\n<p>Some fats are essential to our diets; we often refer to them as the healthy fats, the fats we usually cook our food with. Looking for canola oil? Avocado oil? Extra virgin olive oil? But Mustard Oil in north India while Coconut Oil in South works just fine, as they are available easily in the respective areas. </p>\n\n\n  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/eat3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                                      \n                     \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Let see another example. If a North Indian is asked to include Proteins in his or her diet how must he/she do it? ''Oh! the site says avocado'' & the search begins. Wake up please! Avocados aren''t grown locally in Northern parts of India, they will be scarcely available, mostly very expensive, often under application of chemicals for preservation. So just have your way with the variety of pulses, growing abundantly in Northern India, that are equally laden with protein. </p>\n\n\n                     \n	\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/eat4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n\n\n<p>Eating locally in turn gives a boost to the local farming & agriculture industry. The social benefits of this are borne by the famers and monetary benefits boost the overall economic growth of India. And we all know how it works, economic growth of the country will bring welfare to the people. </p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/eat5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n\n\n\n<p>Other than this, eating locally grown items will reduce the consumption of packaged goods, an industry that today is a leading cause of pollution & also gives an invitation to natural disasters. </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/eat6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n\n\n\n<p>Isn''t it wonderful! Just by being a little more thoughtful about what you eat you can create a positive impact on the environment and the society as a whole! At the end of the day, every individual contribution counts. </p>\n\n<p>So put that jugaadu Indian in you to some good use & know your proteins & carbs better.</p>\n\n<p>Happy Healthy Eating! </p>\n\n<br>\n\n<iframe  class="col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-md-offset-1 col-lg-10 col-lg-offset-1"  width="640" height="400" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Q9oLuzW15jU" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n', 'Artika Singh', 'eat.png', 'eatrec.jpg'),
(56, 'Have a Happy Period!!!', 'Beauty & wellness', 'August 26, 2017', '<p><i>Is there something like a "happy" period?</i></p>\n\n\n<p>Girls all over the world stand united when it comes to talking about this one issue: Menstrual bleeding! </p>\n\n<p>Heavy bleeders, light bleeders, one and all are affected in one way or another during this time of the month. While some girls may feel weak, others may feel little less efficient and some like me can''t help but be cranky! Of course, this temporary behavioral change can be annoying for friends and family around us but only a girl can know the drama and the pain another girl experiences!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>While there is no solution to this uninvited monthly visitor, here are some ways in which you can make your menstruation time a little more cheerful! </p>\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">Drink up!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Staying hydrated is essential! Drinking an ample around of water, approximately 9 cups, will make you feel energized and fresh! It is very important to maintain body fluid levels at this time!</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">Dress for the occasion!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Staying in bed all day will make you feel gloomy. Get out of bed, bathe & wear loose and comfortable clothes, because you might feel bloated up. Avoid light colors for no other reasons except that it''ll be a task to get the stain off if there''s any.</p>\n\n\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nYoga to the rescue!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Nothing drains you like those abdomen cramps. Chocolate is always a savior & please this is no time to count calories, you are losing blood woman ! Still if you are stubborn on not having any then please practice yoga & deep breathing to ease out the pain. Check below link for poses you should practice.</p>\n<p><a href ="https://www.doyouyoga.com/6-yoga-poses-to-relieve-menstrual-cramps-37359/"> https://www.doyouyoga.com/6-yoga-poses-to-relieve-menstrual-cramps-37359/</a></p>\n\n\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">Stay Warm!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Warm drinks & food are a girl''s best friend at this time! Consuming warm items can reduce the swelling in your abdomen which may otherwise cause a lot of pain. And don''t forget your hot water bottle.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nGo vegan</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n\n\n\n\n<p>What? No milk? Well you can always sip on tea! Dairy products can lead to an increase in prostaglandin hormones which can lead to uterus contraction & thus worsen your cramps. Try & keep a check on them, you''ll thank us later. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">Avoid salt</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     	\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Well one of the most soothing things to do is open up a bag of chips & munch your heart out but salty foods make you bloat & we don''t want to add it up while we are already on our menses. So instead of feeling lousier, eat healthy to feel healthy.</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n	\n<h2 class="section-heading">Talk It Out and Shake It Off!</h2>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/p7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                  \n	\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>If there are things troubling you, please must talk to someone. Even if it''s just another mood swing. Speaking to a close and trustworthy person will instantly help you calm down. </p>\n\n<p>So ladies, take good care & pamper yourself all you want because going through that time of month is no piece of cake. Period. ''pun intended''</p>\n', 'Artika Singh', 'period.png', 'periodrec.jpg'),
(58, 'Red burgers & wood fired pizzas anyone?', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'August 21,2017', '<p>We love food, infact few of us live to eat. And the only thing that can beat this love nowadays is the excitement of putting it on Instagram and making our friends jealous and envy us for the rest of their lives. Not just the food but the ambience also adds to our effort of catching that perfect picture.</p>\n\n\n \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/haristo1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p>Haristo Cafe & Pizzeria is one such quaint and cozy cafe that serves a multi-cuisine menu worth trying at least once! One of their unique preparations is the Red Burger which has a juicy patty and delicious toppings inside a reddish-pink bun! Yes, the perfect material for our Instagram stories and feeds. </p>\n\n\n \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/haristo2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p>The burger is served in a whooping eight different options and is absolutely stunning to look at! No! We are not exaggerating.</p>\n\n \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/haristo3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n	<p>And then there are wood-fired hand toasted thin crust oven pizza fully loaded with\nfresh and exotic toppings, lots &amp; lots of cheese &amp; delicious sauces .The smoky\nflavors and the thin crust are beyond perfection.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/haristo4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n <p>The Cafe has looked out for everyone and there are plenty of choices for both vegetarians and meat lovers alike. We would recommend ordering the Crushed Mushroom Burger and the Moroccan Lamb Burger. All their burgers are served with fresh crispy fries and a dip, just the things to make your day awesome and memorable.<p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/haristo5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n                  \n	\n<p>With the perfect ambience, the cafe is a great place to chill and relax with your buddies and have a hearty meal at. They also host regular live sports screenings for all the sports freaks out there which could be a great way to spend time with your crew so head on over! </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Location | Haristo Cafe & Pizzeria, AG-19, Aditya City Centre Mall, Indirapuram</p>\n\n<p>Check out their Facebook Page: </p><p><a href="https://www.facebook.com/IndiHaristo/"> https://www.facebook.com/IndiHaristo</a></p>', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'haristo.jpg', 'haristorec.jpg'),
(57, 'Enjoy Lip Smacking food at this beautiful cafe @ just Rs 96', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'August 28, 2017', '<p>Ever wondered how it would really feel to not bother about looking at THAT side of the menu card, yep, the one with the scary numbers, because you are assured that no matter what, it''s not going to hit hard on your pocket? What if we told you there''s a cafe in town that has everything on their lunch menu priced at just 96 bucks? WHAT? NO! YOU''RE KIDDING. No, we''re not.  </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/cafe1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p>Cafe 96 Square in Krishna Nagar has a special lunch menu apart from their a la carte where you get everything you order for just 96 bucks. AMAZING! Isn''t it? The offer is valid from 12 PM to 4 PM and before you ask, NO, there are no hidden dimensions to this offer and NO, you are not going to run out of options. Coming to their regular a la carte menu, with the items ranging from Gol Gappe to Hummus Pita, they''ve got you covered with almost everything on it and you''re going to love their absolutely delicious and cheesy Thin Crust Pizzas (coz Pizza is Life, Period) and Chilly Garlic Noodles. </p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/cafe2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n  \n\n</span>\n	\n\n<p>And that''s not it. They''re not just some regular cafe with a big-shot menu and a lip smacking offer. Like that wasn''t enough! Cafe 96 Square''s ambience is going to make you fall in love with it the moment you step foot inside.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/cafe3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n	\n\n\n\n\n<p> You''ll be greeted with warm yellow lights with an adorable decor that will make you not want to leave and creative walls that speak for themselves with all the personal messages & comments from visitors. \n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/cafe4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n					<p>\nDelicious pocket friendly food with an awesome ambience, WHAT MORE DO YOU WANT? </p><p>Well we know you don''t but just sitting &amp; eating is boring. So while\nyou wait for your food you can get free games to pass time with\nfriends because it''s an eat &amp; play combo. Ludo, snake &amp; ladder,\nscramble, uno, chess &amp; a lot more.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/cafe5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>\nSo, East Delhi peeps, gather your squad and make lunch plans with them to enjoy some amazing food without caring a damn about the prices. </p>\n\n<p><b>Location | Cafe 96 Square - F-3/20, Krishna Nagar</b><p>', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'cafe96.png', 'caferec.jpg'),
(60, 'Lipstick shades to slay the look AND...their inexpensive alternatives!!!', 'FASHION', 'August 30,2017', '<p>Thrift shopping in case of clothes, shoes and accessories causes no harm, but when it comes to products that will come in direct contact with the skin, one must be very careful!</p>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n1.	Bare Necessities </h2>\n\n<p>Nudes never really go out of fashion and are the perfect choice for the no-make-up-all- natural look for the summer! Here are two of our favourites.</p>\n<p>\n<ul><li>NYX Lip Lingerie Liquid Lipstick- Push up (06) -  (approx.) INR 2,686</li></ul></p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/lip1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Source:<a href="http://www.amazon.in/NYX-Lip-Lingerie-06-Pushup/dp/B01APX1TJ2/ref=sr_1_66?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491915899&sr=1-66\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n	\n\n\n\n\n<p>\n\n<ul><li>ALTERNATIVE!- Make up Revolution (U.K.)- ''The One''- INR 295</li></ul></p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/lip2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Source:<a href="http://www.amazon.in/Makeup-Revolution-AmazingLipstickOne/dp/B00QU3JCYG/ref=sr_1_2?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491916300&sr=1-2&keywords=makeup+revolution\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n	\n\n\n2.	Ravishing Red</h2>\n\n<p>This is an essential shade for all girls. It goes well with almost all outfits and never fails to add an edge to your look!</p>\n<p>\n<ul><li>SUGAR Matte Lip Crayon- Scarlett O'' Hara (01)- INR 799</li></ul>\n</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/lip3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Source:<a href="http://www.amazon.in/Sugar-Matte-Crayon-LipstickScarlett/dp/B01G1HGQ0I/ref=sr_1_2?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491916424&sr=1-2\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>\n<ul><li>Maybelline Color Show Matte- Bold Crimson (M201)- INR 262</li></ul></p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/lip4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Source:<a href="http://www.amazon.in/Maybelline-Color-Show-MatteCrimson/dp/B0148QU03I/ref=lp_1374384031_1_11?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491916485&sr=1-11\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n3.	Think Pink!</h2>\n\n<p>Pink lipsticks are not preferred by all but if the right shade is picked, it can work wonders. \n</p>\n<p>\n<ul><li>Chambor Extreme Matte - Burnt Rose (01)- INR 845</li></ul></p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/lip5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Source:<a href="http://www.amazon.in/Chambor-Extreme-Matte-LipColourProduct/dp/B01LWMN208/ref=sr_1_56?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491917140&sr=1-56\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n\n\n                                               \n<p>\n<ul><li>Maybelline Color Show- Crushed Candy (103)- INR 244</li></ul></p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/lip6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted ">Source:<a href="http://www.amazon.in/Maybelline-Color-Show-LipstickBling/dp/B00W4ZB21A/ref=lp_1374384031_1_22?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491916485&sr=1-22\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n4.	Get Mauve-ing</h2>\n\n<p>For special occasions and formal events don''t hesitate to use a dark color lipstick. It can really help in holding the outfit together and adding a