Lakme-Enrich-Satins-ColorShade/dp/B0185I8Y6U/ref=sr_1_7?s=beauty&ie=UTF8&qid=1491921998&sr=1-7&keywords=orange+lipstick\n">www.amazon.in</a></span>\n\n\n\n<p>\n\n\nPS: Don''t kill us for a little up & down in the prices. But hurry up while the beauties are still up for grabs. </p>', 'Artika Singh', 'lip.jpg', 'liprec.jpg'),
(64, 'Get #MADOVERMOMO', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'September 15, 2017', '<p>We Delhites absolutely love our Momos and don''t miss any chance we get to enjoy this hot, delicious snack any time throughout the day with our friends & family. Those mini snack breaks are something we definitely cherish and they have a special place in our heart somewhere, and of course, our tummy too! What if we told you there''s a whole festival being celebrated which is dedicated to only one thing, YES! MOMOS.  </p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/madmomo1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n\n<p>All you Momo lovers out there need to listen to this. There''s a crazy momo festival going on at Cafe Lungta in Gurgaon that you''re definitely going to LOVE! Known as #MADOVERMOMO, that we sure as hell are, these guys have lined up a bunch of momos belonging to various regions. </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/madmomo2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>Everything, ranging from Nepali Dharun Ko style, Dharamshala''s Dasha Ko, Chanakyapuri style to Majnu Ka Tila specialities, and many more!! Name it, and they''ve got it here for you. Whether it''s cottage cheese filling or juicy minced chicken with some coriander that you''re looking for, Cafe Lungta has your back. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/madmomo3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Each plate that you order here comes with 8 pieces PLUS not 1, not 2, but 3 diverse, flavorful dips! YUM.</p>\n<p>There''s no way in hell we''re gonna miss this and we''re totally heading over to check out this #MADOVERMOMO festival right away. Hope to see you all there. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/madmomo4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>When | Ongoing Till End of September</p>\n<p>Where | Cafe Lungta - Ground Floor, SCO 23, Sector 15, Gurgaon</p>\n<p>Timings | 12:30 PM - 11 PM</p>\n<p>Entry | Free </p>\n<p>Check Out Their FB Page| <a href="https://www.facebook.com/cafelungta"> https://www.facebook.com/cafelungta</a></p>\n\n\n\n\n', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'madmomos.jpg', 'madmomorec.jpg'),
(59, 'Escape boredom with Escape Games', 'ADVENTURE', 'August 29,2017', '<p>Like staying indoors, cozying around doing nothing? While we are at it, let''s add a twist to it. How about you get locked in a room without a key? And you just got 60 minutes to get out before something bad happens. Just 60 minutes to escape, making your way through plenty of quest items, locks and tasks. The mere thought gives you an adrenaline rush, isn''t it? Being trapped in a room and frantically hunting for clues to save your life or to reach the treasure, feeling Indiana Jones already?</p>\n\n\n<p>How much wits can you test with online games? Witness your skills, sharp eyes & quick action in real. And NO, you don''t have to be an absolute genius to work these out. Designed by a team of psychologists & game makers, the games ensured loads of fun for everyone. It''s all about team effort. So work together & escape. Getting locked was never so much FUN! </p>\n<p>This amazing concept is brought to you by the company "Ctrl.Shift.Esc" and is suitable for everyone, be it your friends or family, any corporate event or any special occasion. Let''s go through the current ideas.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n1.	Battle of thrones:</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/escape1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted"> \nSource: <a href="http://www.escaperoomsindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/bot.jpg">Escape Rooms India</a></span>\n\n\n<p>Oh yes, "WINTER IS HERE", gotta kill the white walkers. What do we need for that? Yes don''t scream please, I hear it ''Dragonglass''. So come help your favourite Jon snow to defeat the Night King and claim the throne.</p><p><ul>\n<li>	Time: 60 minutes</li>\n<li>Level: Intermediate</li>\n<li>2-8 Players</li>\n<li>Location: Escape rooms, Hauz Khas Village</li></ul>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n2.	The Safehouse:</h2>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/escape2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted"> \nSource: <a href="http://www.escaperoomsindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/game.jpg"> Escape Rooms India</a> </span>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Mr 007 has gone missing on a secret mission to identify a mole. So try & find the mole in 60 minutes else suffer the same fate as Mr Bond.</p><p><ul>\n<li>Time: 60 minutes</li>\n<li>Level: Beginner</li>\n<li>2-8 Players</li>\n<li>Location: Escape rooms, Hauz Khas Village & Sector 29 Gurgaon</li></ul>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n3.	The Quarantine Zone:</h2>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/escape3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted"> \nSource: <a href="http://www.escaperoomsindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/quarantine.png\n"> Escape Rooms India</a></span>\n\n\n<p>\nNation is hit with a deadly epidemic & people are turning into Zombies. Find a cure or be ready to join the living dead. Not for children below 10 years, don''t want them to have bad dreams, do we? </p><p><ul>\n<li>Time: 60 minutes</li>\n<li>Level: Advanced</li>\n<li>2-8 Players</li>\n<li>Location: Escape rooms, Hauz Khas Village</li></ul>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n4.	Room # 7:</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/escape4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted "> \nSource: <a href="http://www.escaperoomsindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/Room_7.jpg">Escape Rooms India</a></span>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>So you check into a motel Norman Bates'' & soon realize that you are not going to make it alive. Your only chance is to solve its first murder. Requires supervision for children below 12 years.</p><p><ul>\n<li>Time: 60 minutes</li>\n<li>Level: Advanced</li>\n<li>2-10 Players</li>\n<li>Location: Escape rooms, Sector 29, Gurgaon</li></ul>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n5.	The Taken Souls:</h2>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/escape5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    <span class="caption text-muted"> \nSource: <a href="http://www.escaperoomsindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/taken-souls_CSE_desc.jpg"> Escape Rooms India </a></span>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>Time for some pirate action! So you are captured on the ship of the dead. Free your soul or "part of the crew, part of the ship". Hurry before the crew wakes up! </p><p><ul>\n<li>Time: 60 minutes</li>\n<li>Level: Intermediate</li>\n<li>2-10 Players</li>\n<li>Location: Escape rooms, Sector 29, Gurgaon</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>Pay attention to every detail and leave no stone unturned! Remember the clock is ticking...60...59...58...! BOOM</p>\n\n<p><b>Contact details:</b></p>\n\n<p>+919654743138</p><p>\nHKV: 	011-26564072</p><p>\nGGN: 	0124 4175424</p>\n\n<p><b>Booking link:</b><p>\n<a href="http://www.escaperoomsindia.com/game-rooms/">http://www.escaperoomsindia</a></p>', 'Chetna Dhull', 'escape.jpg', 'escaperec.jpg'),
(61, 'Live the Desi feels this weekend @ This Farm Retreat in Gurugram', 'ADVENTURE', 'August 30,2017', '<p>Living in the city, thousands of people around, lavish & huge buildings but still nothing beats the desi feels we witnessed in our villages or farms or back in the hometown. City has so much to offer but not enough to make up for the homely environment we miss.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Still think of waking up to the sounds of chirping birds instead of honking cars, gurgling water amidst lush green fields instead of your packed washroom? Yeah we all do but never have enough time off daily routine to plan a decent holiday.</p>\n<p>The Golden Creepers Farm Retreat in Gurugram has come to your aid by offering you everything you need with a perfect blend of desi, relaxed and adventurous vacation with your loved ones.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/farm1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                   \n\n\n\n<p>Spread across a 45 acres of abundantly green farm fields, it provides you an earthly feel with everything that you experience there, be it drinking fresh water pulled out straight from the ground or enjoying long walks by the natural, undulating landscape. You can sit here for hours gazing at the blazing sunset, who doesn''t love sunsets, while often spotting some magnificent sights of birds from the adjoining Sultanpur Bird Sanctuary. Sounds just perfect, don''t it?</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/farm2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n\n\n\n<p>Don''t worry about missing home as the food served here is surely going to make you feel homely. Along with their delicious paranthas, Rajma Chawal and some chai and pakodas to enjoy the vibrant evenings they also have a number of activities that you can take part in like tilling, ploughing, sowing, milking cows and feeding farm animals. Hop on the tractor, relive your childhood by taking a mud bath or get on the Commando Bridge, one thing is for sure, you''re never going to get bored of this place. And that''s not it. With pottery, painting, learning to make lassi, archery, barbeques, bonfires AND MUCH MORE, they''re surely going to give you all the desi feels.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/farm3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n\n<p>Get here with your family or friends and get all rejuvenated for this is one of the most happening places to enjoy a desi weekend getaway.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/farm4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                    \n<p>Location | Golden Creepers Farm Retreat - Village Chandu, Near Sultanpur Bird Sanctuary</p>\n\n<p>Check out their Website:<a href="\nhttp://www.goldencreepers.com/"> http://www.goldencreepers.com/\n</a></p>\n\n', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'farm.jpg', 'farmrec.jpg'),
(63, 'For a Perfect First Trip!', 'Travel', 'August 30,2017', '\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">Let me help you</h2>\n\n<p>One of my favourite philanthropists, Oprah Winfrey said, "The biggest adventure you can take is to live the life of your dreams." I personally believe that there is no truer definition to adventure than that. Some of the beautiful memories of life are fabricated deep within our hearts while travelling to expedient places. It is as if your uncanny determination for an adventure is supported by the nature if you have the will, and want it badly.</p> \n\n\n<p>\n\nSo wherever I go, I go with all my heart. My travel experiences left me speechless but never in my wildest dreams have I ever thought that I would become a storyteller. Only in my case, it is not just the story I am going to share but some of the essential and crucial things one should certainly carry along with them. </p>\n<p><b>\n1.	Choose only important luggage:</b><p>\n<p>More you shortlist, more you have to carry. Hope you are not trekking with same. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p><b>\n2.	Wear comfortable clothing:</b></p>\n<p>\nCome on, who''s gonna judge you for choosing loose wear but your body will thank you for letting it breathe. So go crazy with t-shirts, shorts & joggers.  Also check destination weather for being too hot or cold. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n<p><b>\n\n3.	Travelling is a never-ending mission & you need energy to move: </b></p>\n\n<p>Carry sufficient energy bars, crackers, nuts or any items you feel like eating to rejuvenate your tired body.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n\n\n<p><b>\n\n4.	Water fuels life, keep your engines full:</b></p>\n<p>How silly will it be to ask people for water? I know you can purchase it but why not put your water bottle to use to ensure clean water throughout your journey.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n\n\n\n<p><b>\n\n5.	First Aid Kit because safety does not happen by accident: </b></p>\n<p>You never know when you would be doing random gravity checks, falling straight on your face. So keep some antiseptic, cotton, band aids & any other medicine you feel is necessary. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n\n\n<p><b>\n\n6.	Identity Card, cash & proper docs: </b></p>\n<p>So you venture deep into a forest without permission & then suddenly stopped by an officer to prove your identity & you just end up with "Do I look like a terrorist or paddler" looks. Please carry your ID-cards, required cash & ATM cards and anything else you feel is necessary.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n	\n\n\n<p><b>\n\n7.	Your small carry-on bag: </b></p><p>\nJust for the items you need to keep handy - your tickets, charger, headphones, power bank, camera, small torch, sun glasses & stuff.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/te7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p><b>\n\n8.	Toiletry bag: </b></p><p>\nYes, can''t forget it. Need the necessary things - toothbrush, toothpaste, comb, soap, sanitizer, deodorant, face wash, lotion, wet tissues, shampoo & sunscreen. Carry mini pouches of whatever possible. </p>\n                     \n	\n\n\n\n<p><b>\n\n9.	Others: </b></p><p>\nA raincoat if weather is drizzly, a sleeping bag if you like going without plans, a neck pillow for that long bus journey, eye mask if can''t sleep in light & lots of excitement for a great trip.</p>\n                 \n                     \n	', 'Geeta Sowmya', 'te.jpg', 'terec.jpg'),
(62, 'No black & white! We want colour!!!', 'FASHION', 'August 30,2017', '<p>Life is too short to be boring. With things running at such fast pace we want to tag along obviously. We like exploring and experimenting. And when it comes to looks there are no boundaries to go wild. Crazy hairdos, new tattoos, funky clothes, hap shoes are just ways to transform and bring out the best in us. So let''s talk about hair colour variants men can try after all you are no less than women when it comes to being stylish.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n1.	Dark black:</h2><p>\nWell if you have medium to dark skin tones, go for it. It really accentuates your facial features & of course makes your hair look voluminous. And on top of that you mom is happy that you went for black & nothing super funky *wink*.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                   \n	\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n2.	Dark brown:</h2>\n<p>Considered as one of the most formal hair colour it makes you stand out. Perfect for all skin tones , go for it if you just want to experiment with hair colour and want to try a safe new look.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n3.	Golden brown:</h2><p>\nIf you are looking for a more vibrant and dynamic look go for golden brown. Perfect for light to medium skin tones and your brown eyes, it gives you the quintessential cool dude look.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n         <span class="caption text-muted">Credit: Hairstyles for men</span>            \n                     \n	\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n4.	Chocolate brown:</h2><p>\nIf you have really thick hair, go for this. Don''t worry if you have light hairs, just apply a thickening serum to give that thick texture. Perfect for all skin tones, it''s a truly dreamy hair colour.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n5.	Caramel:</h2><p>\nIf you are on the warmer side of skin tone, please oh please go for this. Like the name, it looks delicious on men. The rich colour provides great texture to your hair & highlight your eyes as well. So go on, sweep women of their feet with your new look.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n                     \n  <span class="caption text-muted">Credit: Hairstyles Daily</span>    	\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n6.	Copper brown:</h2>\n<p>So confused about what to go for your curls, look up for copper brown. It just adds life to each individual curl. Straight hairs can also be coloured with it but try to keep them short and little messy. Works wonders with light skin tone.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair6.jpg" alt="">\n                   \n\n				 </div>\n                     <span class="caption text-muted">Credit: Men''s Hairstyles Club</span>  \n                     \n	 \n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n7.	Red:</h2><p>\nDeep cool reds are something all complexions can work with, though preferred for light tones. If you like dark t-shirts then go for absolute darker shades else slight lighter ones. Full of vibrancy, it would require some serious guts but promise you''ll stand out.</p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n					\n					  <span class="caption text-muted">Credit: Hairstyles Daily</span>    \n<h2 class="section-heading">\n8.	Steel grey:</h2><p>\nWant to hide your greys & look graceful, this is your calling. Look sharp, sexy & portray yourself as the boss. A dark shade of hair colour with steel grey undertone looks great on lighter & medium complexions.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/menhair8.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                    \n      <span class="caption text-muted">Credit: Men''s Hairstyles Club</span>             ', 'Chetna Dhull', 'menhair.jpg', 'menhairrec.jpg'),
(66, 'Wine & Women', 'LIFESTYLE', 'September 15,2017', '<p>CAN I BUY YOU A DRINK? </p>\n<p>\nNo Thank You</p>\n\n<p>She is beautiful, she is uniquely talented, and she is patient. Who is she?  She is every woman out there who deserves to be encouraged and needs to be protected. She can''t go for late night outings; she can''t do whatever she wishes to do and she should abide by rules. The boundaries for women in India are incessant. </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/ww1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>Buying and consuming alcohol by women is something frowned upon in most of the places, even in metros. As Mr Bachchan quoted in Pink "Consuming liquor represents a bad character, for women. Not for men, for them it''s just a health hazard". </p>\n\n\n<p>Women share equal responsibility with men in this modern India, so it''s not a big deal if they want to have their share of fun. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/ww2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>Regrettably, a female cannot walk straight into a liquor shop filled with men because it would only result in her inconvenience and is a matter of sacrificing her safety or dignity. No matter the location of the shop, she cannot enjoy her evening booze without feeling uncomfortable or being centre of attraction. </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/ww3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>I am not judging all of the service providers, some serve you first seeing you alone, kudos to them, but some take advantage of the situation. I wish for shops that would actually let female squad buy or drink anything of their choice without a sneaky stare. Fortunately, I came across a few places in Delhi where a modern femme fatale can figure out her favourite for the evening. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>La Cave, Select City walk, Delhi </li>\n<li>High Times ,across Delhi</li>\n<li>Wine and Beer Shop, across NCR </li>\n<li>Spencer''s - The Wine & Spirits Section, across Gurgaon</li>\n<li>Lakeforest Wines, across Gurgaon</li>\n<li>Sugar & Spice - Le Marche, across NCR</li></ul>\n\n   <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/ww4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>Hmm. Quite the options, aren''t they? What are you waiting for if you are in a mood for a booze? Not having to get intimidated under the scrutinizing gazes of critics, you can take your potion in peace.                </p>                    	\n\n', 'Geeta Sowmya', 'winewomen.jpg', 'wwrec.jpg'),
(70, 'Book your next table at\r\nFig & Maple!', 'FOOD & BEVERAGES', 'August 28,2017', '<p>Have you checked out this cafe cum library in GK II?</p>\n\n<p>"Fig & Maple" with their minimalistic interior decor style and aesthetic plates of mouth-watering food will own your heart at the very first go. </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p><b>Where?</b></p>\n\n<p>M-27, E Block Rd, Block M, Greater Kailash II, Greater Kailash, New Delhi.<p>\n<p>On weekends and other such holidays make sure you get a reservation at 08800665975. </p>\n\n<p><b>Nearest Metro Station:</b> Hauz Khas / Kailash Colony</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>A beautiful rooftop with plants & shimmering lights along with a beautiful mini library, well what better can you ask on any given morning. </p>\n\n\n<p><b>Let''s talk about the food ...\n</b></p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p><b>...Well, before the food, let''s talk about the chef who creates this magic!</b><p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n\n<p><b>Radhika Khandelwal,</b> the owner of the famous Ivy & Bean at Shahpur Jat is also the mastermind behind fig & Maple, where she has herself curated the interesting forest themed menu.\nShe recalls that it was when she was pursuing psychology and hairdressing, she also took up a job at a restaurant and that''s where it all began!!!</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>The menu is obviously tempting & takes you faraway places as soon as you have a glance at the menu. Central park, little Italy, columbus circle, dolores park, madison square, brooklyn, napa valley are some of the names your eyes will scroll through. </p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>We recommend their signature fig & maple salad along with delicious banoffee waffles, buttermilk waffles with chicken & little Italy omelet. Wait don''t feel full already, yet to walk through the mains. With variety of pastas, rice, grills & platters it sure is going to make you hungry for more. And please oh please don''t check out before sinking your teeth in the ever soft lamb chops. </p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig7.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Also forget about the days when your beverage gets hotter while you are gobbling up your food. Just enjoy chilled beer or smoothies with your personal ice box at your table. No more washing down the throat with hot stuff, drink like they are meant to be. Put the final foody nail in your stomachy coffin with chocolate & cotton cheesecake, just melts in your mouth.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/fig8.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>So grab your laptop, get off your lazy bum and head over here for a refreshing environment, free wi-fi and a complimentary in-house brewed coffee. Spending some me time was never this delicious, yum!</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'Artika Singh', 'fig.jpg', 'figrec.jpg'),
(68, '5 Things Every Girl Should Stop Saying\n', 'Entertainment', 'September 16,2017', ' \n\n	  \n<p>Girls let''s face it, there are some silly things we keep saying to ourselves and also to our female counterparts, which we should definitely avoid.\nWe should not forget that we are confident & independent women!</p>\n\n<p>Following is the list of 5 things every girl should steer clear of:</p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n1.	"I wish I was like her"</h2>\n\n\n<p>You are perfect the way you are. Being jealous of someone''s dress or body features will not make you any better? Be happy with what you''ve got and be confident about yourself. There''s no one like you.</p>\n\n\n\n           \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/girl1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n2. "That girl is such a slut!"</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We girls already have so much to deal with on daily basis then why add this girl-on-girl hatred? Live and let live should be your mantra for life! Stop hate, spread love.</p>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/girl2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n3. "I hate periods!"</h2>\n\n<p>Getting periods on time every month is not something to get upset about, it is something to feel proud about because there are many girls out there who do not get their periods regularly. In fact, regular periods and a good flow means you''re fit and it also means you''re not pregnant. *phew* \nPamper yourself, keep kicking.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/girl3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n4. "I feel so incomplete without him"</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Really girl? How does he make you complete? You were complete before he came to your life and you still are. Don''t let anyone walk all over you. So stop crying and start celebrating yourself! You go girl!</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/girl4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\n5. "Do I look fat?"</h2>\n\n<p>So what if you look fat? Will fast food chains start selling diet burgers or will cheese become less attractive? No!</p>\n\n<p>Be confident about your body type and stop body shaming yourself. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/girl5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>"Real women are fat. And thin. And both, and neither, and otherwise - Hanne Blank"</p>\n\n\n								\n									\n\n', 'The Editor', 'girl.jpg', 'girlrec.jpg');
