(69, 'Feel like going Tarzan in the jungle?', 'ADVENTURE', 'September 16,2016', '\n\n<p>You do! Then this adventure sport is for you!</p>\n<p><b>Zip lining:</b> one of the most popular adventure sports that''s going to make your adrenaline rush faster than when you forget to delete your browser history, don''t worry, we''ve all been there.</p>\n<p> Zip lining consists of a pulley suspended on a cable, usually made of stainless steel, mounted on an incline. Obviously propelled by gravity, it is designed to enable a user to zap from the top to the bottom of the inclined cable by holding & attaching to the freely rolling pulley. YES! The way Captain America did it in The First Avenger. WE KNOW RIGHT? SO COOL. These zip lines are available in many forms, though they are most commonly used as a means of entertainment. \nNow, the organizing team has divided this sport into different formats depending upon the varying distance.</p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nZip 1: Eagle''s PlayStation (400m) </h2>\n\n<p>Lets you scout the entire side of the mountain covering the spectacular view of the Neemrana Fort-Palace, making you feel like an Eagle exploring the unending skies. </p>\n\n \n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/zip1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\n\nZip 2: To Qila Slammer (330m) </h2>\n\n<p>Feast your eyes with the astonishing views of Rajasthan countryside along the crest of the Aravalli Mountains after being launched from an old lookout point and flying towards an ancient hill fort. </p>\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/zip2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nZip 3: "Goodbye Mr Bond..." (250m) </h2>\n<p>It may be their love for Mr. Bond that they have named this zip line after this very famous immortal dialogue by The Goldfinger or just the thrill it promises you. Well, there''s only one way to find out! </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/zip3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nZip 4: The Big B (175m) </h2>\n<p>It wouldn''t be hard to guess after whom this zipline is named. Yes, Mr.Amitabh Bachchan zipped from this very spot into the Fort-Palace during the shoot of the film "Major Sahab" and it''s surely gonna make you crave for some more adventure. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/zip4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nZip 5: Pussy Galore (90m) </h2>\n<p>This is the shortest of all of their zips and designed to give you an essence of zip lining after which you can opt for longer and more adventurous zips. Being named after one of the best Bond girls, its sure sweet & fast like her. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/zip5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>Worried about prices? Yes, we can''t ignore the M factor! Thrill is one thing but empty pockets are surely devastating. Don''t worry, you are sorted.</p>\n<p>For Adult: Rs.2199</p>\n<p>For Child: Rs.1899</p>\n<p>You can buy tickets at <a href="http://www.flyingfox.asia/">http://www.flyingfox.asia/</a></p>\n<p>So, Delhi, get ready for a 100km road trip and head to Neemrana fort where this awesome adventure sport awaits you.</p>\n', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'zip.jpg', 'ziprec.jpg'),
(67, 'Sabka Ghar ! Appu Ghar !', 'ADVENTURE', 'September 16,2016', ' <p>NCR region is the perfect blend of western infrastructure and technology along with loads of cultural diversity. It is the best place to explore & is quite famous for being ''all in one'', right from historical monuments, street foods, adventure islands, resorts, theatres & what not, it is just loaded with stuff. When the weekend hits, it''s quite natural to want to get away from the hustle bustle of the city. So no more worries finding the perfect spot for the whole family - check out <b>Appu Ghar.</b></p> \n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\nLots to see and do:</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/appu1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>It is often said that life is better at the beach. Then why don''t you stretch out at the shores of the <b>Oysters beach?</b> This is located behind HUDA city metro station and it is renowned for its amazing water rides and their electrifying experiences. It also indulges you with a variety of mind-blowing activities coupled with the soothing melody of music, dance and fun.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\nFeel like flying?</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/appu2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>No wings but wish to fly? Then please try <b>The Skyfall</b> one of the tallest rides in India. The experience would let your dreams take flight and the feeling of adrenaline pumping through your veins would cause jitters creep within your spine. Pirate Station, OMG, Typhoon Tunnel are the other thrilling water rides that you can enjoy here. Around 15 water rides and other attractions such as rain dance, lazy river and wave pool are surely hard to miss.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">Craving for the so called ''me time''?</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/appu3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>It is essential to spend some time to renew and relax, after all the soul sucking Monday is in line. What can be better to boost yourself than a soothing spa? The incredible experience one gets while feeling the stretch of the muscles fused with a lovely music has no words to describe it.</p>\n\n<h2 class="section-heading">\n\nCalling all foodies out there</h2>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/appu4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p>It''s often said that the people who love to eat are always the best people. So all you best people, be prepared to be attacked by the aroma of 4 multi-speciality restaurants at the Crazy River food court - Southern Bay, Aroma Coast, Tidal Tadka and Langkawi Bay . Apart from them there is Low Tide Buffet restaurant & Hi-Tide Bar serving world class cuisine and tantalizing cocktails.</p>\n<p>So experience fun like never before. Take your family out, see your kids having the ultimate experience and hit the spa yourself. Can''t find a better place, it''s the whole package.</p>\n\n<p>Check out more at <a href=http://appughargurugram.com/>\nhttp://appughargurugram.com/</a></p>\n', 'Geeta Sowmya', 'appu.jpg', 'appurec.jpg'),
(71, 'Live to laugh & laugh to live!', 'ENTERTAINMENT', 'September 16,2017', ' \n<p>\n\n"I relish the fact that you''ve mustard the strength to ketchup to me."</p>\n<p>Yeah go on say what a PJ but can''t wipe that grin off your face, can you? Just trying to share a laugh in a world where people have forgotten how to smile altogether. Busy life schedules, work tensions, increasing communication gaps & with increasing dependency on mobiles, people have somehow forgotten how to laugh. While we are at it, enjoy one more, </p>\n<p><i>"What was Forrest Gump''s email password? ""1forrest1""</i></p>\n<p>All this to remind you that laughing is as important as breathing if you want to live a long & healthy life. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/clc1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n<p>So if you bored of visiting the same pub every time, ordering the same liquor & dancing  to the same tunes then take a break & do something different this time. Get high on life for a change, laugh your heart out & yeah meet people who share your sense of humour.</p>\n<p>Go & spend your evening with Canvas Laugh Club, you''ll thank me later. No loud music & no bright lights but only laughter & smiling faces all around.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/clc2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>As their website quotes-</p>\n<p>"Apart from the stand-up comedy, what makes the Canvas Laugh Club the ultimate evening destination, there are exquisite theatre performances like the Vagina Monologues, Bakchod, Improv Comedy, Children''s Theatre and much more. Come discover the hilarious world of the Canvas Laugh Club and see the funny side of life!"</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10 col-lg-10" src="img/clc3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>The live experience is just rejuvenating, a perfect place to catch a break. Give your mind some dose of real comedy which will challenge your comic quotient.</p>\n\n<p>Go visit Canvas Laugh Club at Cyber hub, Gurgaon to experience something different, satisfy your laughter buds, just have smiles all around & know what it''s like to laugh your lungs out.</p>\n<p>So make your bookings & be prepared for a blast.</p>\n<p><a href="https://www.canvaslaughclub.com"> https://www.canvaslaughclub.com</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://www.eventshigh.com/delhi/canvas+laugh+club"> https://www.eventshigh.com</a></p>\n<p><a href="https://in.bookmyshow.com/venue/canvas-laugh-club-at-the-people-company/CLCD"> https://in.bookmyshow.com-CLC</a></p>\n\n', 'Chetna Dhull', 'clc.jpg', 'clcrec.jpg'),
(75, 'Party all night !', 'Nightlife', 'September 21,2017', '<p><i><center>Already checked out all the places in HKV? Here''s where you should go next.</center></i></p>\n\n\n<p>Pubs play "abhi to party shuru hui hai" at 9 pm and generally shut down at 1 am. What about the after party, where do we do the drunk conversations with our friends. ''Congratulations on being drunk, now please go home''. Whattt ! That''s rude.</p>\n\n<p>You expect us to drive home this drunk, late night, all alone. And imagine the horror of that friend whose house you go for after party. All that noise, smoke from fags, neighbours complaining and let''s not get started on the washroom scenes. And the never ending hunts for booze as we are always short.</p>\n\n<p>But fear no more guys, we have a solution to your never ending party plans & special occasions.\n</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">\nTHE ELECTRIC ROOM IS HERE!</h2>\n\n<p>The Electric Room opened up in Delhi in the month of March in the basement of the Lodhi Hotel, Delhi! This is the place of your dream party, the place to lose yourself in.</p>\n\n<p>This is where you''d want to spend your nine-to-four, we mean 9 p.m. to 4 a.m. , yup they took "4 baj gye lekin party abhi baki hai" quite literally. So feel free to spend the devil''s hour here doing devilish things with your friends. That''s 7 hours of non-stop fun with music, awesome food & a bar that never sleeps.</p>\n\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/night1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n<p>A mystically lit stairway makes the entry very appealing, leaving you in awe & amazement. As you enter you are hit with peppy music, energetic crowd, a stage for live music & a heavenly bar. The mild yellow lighting makes all your blues go away and your mood mellows down to lose itself in the fun & excitement.</p>\n\n<p>The place serves a variety of drinks, tantalizing cocktails, and numerous appetizing food items from their high-end menu. It''s a perfect combination of a vibrant atmosphere with soothing ambience. </p>\n\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/night2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n\n<h2 class="section-heading"> THEY HAVE LIVE MUSIC!</h2>\n\n<p>They have live gigs almost every day of the week. They have pop Tuesdays, Jazz Wednesdays, electric Thursdays added with Gymkhana priced drinks for friends & members & the weekends are a sight. </p>\n                 \n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/night3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/night4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n                  <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/night5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n <div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/night6.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n\n\n\n\n<p>\n\nIt''s like a never ending party. Now who needs weekend to party when you have such great options on weekdays?</p>\n\n<p><b>Wondering how to get there?</b></p>\n\n<p>Well if you''re cutting on the traffic and taking the metro, the closest stations will be:</p>\n<p><b> \nINA<br> \nJLN Stadium<br>\nKhan Market<br>\nJangpura\n<br>\n</b></p>\n<p>\nAlternatively, you can take a smooth ride in a cab to this lounge, situated very close to India Gate.</p>\n\n<p>Log on to their facebook page :<a href=" https://www.facebook.com/electricroomlodhi/"> https://www.facebook.com-electricroomlodhi</a>\nfor updates!</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n', 'Artika Singh', 'night.jpg', 'nightrec.jpg'),
(76, 'Disco Disco.Ssshhhhhh!It''s silent', 'Nightlife', 'September 21,2017', '<p>If you have visited Punjabi Bagh lately, then you might have observed the Rajouri garden pub-fever slowly spreading to it with numerous new restaurants and discos popping up. Punjabi Bagh is gradually turning into a foodie''s hub and we couldn''t have been happier.</p> \n<p>You all must have seen Ranbir Kapoor and Anushka Sharma starrer ''Ae Dil Hai Mushkil.. The "Breakup Song" from the movie is such a peppy number and people groove to this song as soon as the DJ hits it. Remember them dancing with headphones on? Kind of like your personal DJ! Do we have to go to London or Goa to experience it? Nah! It boosts our excitement to a whole new level when something such as Headphones Cafe pops up at Punjabi Bagh. </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/disco1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>''Headphones'' is an initiative taken by Nitin Bhojwani and Divik Bajaj. The guests are handed over a glowing headphone on their arrival which allows them to switch between 3 different music options. From EDM to Sufi to Bollywood chartbusters, the list in never ending. With the option to choose your own music, it''s sure to give you crazy party feels.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/disco2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p>Along with the mind blowing concept, they have some delicious food, drinks and sheesha menu in the house which in only going to make you craving for more. So plan your brunch, lunch, happy hours or dinner, they are all set to take you by storm.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/disco3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p>Their menu looks perfect with lip smacking dishes. You ask for it and they have it - pizzas, burgers, pastas, biryanis, north Indian, chinese, sea food, and a long list of veg & non-veg starters. Let me give you the essence of some of their must try items!</p>\n\n<p><b>Veg Classic Nachos</b></p>\n<p>Loaded with cheese, onions, tomatoes and jalapenos, this is the perfect nacho dish your taste buds can get acquainted to. </p>\n<p><b>Tandoori Vodka Raan 	</b></p>\n<p>This is one of their specials that you just can''t miss. Tender pieces of chicken marinated in spices and vodka, this one is super delectable. The mint chutney and onions on the side will really amp up the whole dish, not to mention the portion size is quite ample, which is another plus.</p>\n<p><b>Chilli Chicken</b></p>\n<p>This spicy diced chicken with onions and bell peppers in hot chilli garlic sauce will really make you drool. Neither too spicy nor too bland.</p>\n<p>Yes yes, I am coming to the drinks menu.Hm what can I say, see for yourself.</p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/disco4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p><b>Aacharito</b></p>\n<p>Gin, mix aachar, mint & lime cocktail.Now that sounds just crazy & pickle-y.</p>\n<p><b>Mexicano</b></p>\n<p>Tequila,gol gappa ghol & kala khatta cocktail.Gol gappa & chuski lovers please line up for this new way of having your favourite food.</p>\n<p><b>Too Special</b></p>\n<p>Rum, saffron & faluda shot.Who needs some un-convectional dessert to make you bit tipsy.</p>\n<p><b>One for the Road</b></p>\n<p>Vodka,rochak & roohafza ice cocktail.Like can you please leave something out of the menu.</p>\n<p>So no more fights with friends over choosing the location as per individual music taste. This is your answer to everything. Go grab your gang & party with your glittery headphones on.  </p>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/disco5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n\n<p><b>Location:</b> 1, Club Road, Punjabi Bagh</p>\n<p><b>Timings:</b> 12PM - 1AM</p>\n<p><b>Cost for two:</b> Rs 1,200 (plus taxes)</p>\n\n\n\n\n', 'Tanishq Agarwal', 'disco.jpg', 'discorec.jpg'),
(77, 'Make your weekends exciting', 'Travel', 'September 22,2017', '\n\n<p>You know what Socrates uttered to busy people? </p>\n<p>"Beware the barrenness of a busy life".</p> \n<p>I know you are thinking we cannot just avoid being busy because we have so much to do in life and so many responsibilities to attend to. Right? However better days come at the doorstep of every busy individual in form of Saturdays and Sundays. Even though Delhi sports many tourist places inside it, true to the notion that this metropolitan city offers all, it also gives one with a plethora of options for a weekend getaway. Make sure you enjoy your weekend fully before its poof and a snap. It is time to take off for the weekend and below is the list of some of the best weekends getaways that I would like to share with you from my experience.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">Mussoorie - Queen of Hill Stations:</h2>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hill1.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>I visited this beautiful hill station with my friends. We did a stopover at many prominent attractions. Among them was Kempty Falls, where the scenic beauty was stunning especially during winter. The coolest thing was taking a bath under the waterfalls and the warm fluid cascading along the surface of our body made the experience tantalizing. There was a road that stretched like a camel''s lump and hence named Camel''s back road. Morning walk on this road during the chilly weather was one of the best experiences I had. Trekking activities were just power packed and the destinations one reaches after the achievement like Cloud''s End, were mesmerizing. Mussoorie is truly a Queen of Hill Stations. Mid-march to Mid-November would be the best days to visit this lovely hill station. </p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">NAUKUCHIATAL - Lake of Nine Corners:</h2>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hill2.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>This small hill station in Nainital is a perfect getaway for the weekend if you are a nature lover. It is also a challenging hill station with adventures like paragliding & paddling as well as a paradise to migratory birds. After a session of bird watching we took to paragliding. The view was amazing from above and the lakes surrounding the place were breathtaking. The myths & stories of Sat Tal were fascinating & the locals told them with full excitement. Over all, it was a thrilling experience and a refreshing weekend encapsulating the depths of this lake.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">Lansdowne:</h2>\n\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hill3.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>Tucked away in a remote corner of Pauri Garhwal district, this small hill station is a popular town with many tourist attractions. Jungle Safari was one of the best rides in the wild. To observe wild animals in their natural habitat in the Himalayas was exhilarating. Moreover, the view of Majestic Himalayas and the Shivalik Ranges was beautiful from a small hilltop known as Tiffin top. I should say I thoroughly enjoyed the tranquil atmosphere of the Bhullaka Lake and it was a surprise to me that this lake was maintained by the Indian Army. You can even spot them in the vicinity. </p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">Sariska Tiger Reserve, Alwar:</h2>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hill4.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>If you are up for a glimpse of the Wild Cat and the diverse wildlife, then this place is for you. You do not have to visit Africa to experience it, Sariska National Park provides you just that. The safari was arranged by the Sariska personnel. Luckily, I caught a glimpse of the tiger while undergoing the ride. It was the first time I saw a tiger in the open and was a little nervous but I guess this is the best way to see them, in their natural habitat. This place also has many multi-cuisine restaurants to satiate your hunger before going for sightseeing.</p>\n<h2 class="section-heading">Bharatpur Bird Sanctuary:</h2>\n<div class="row"><img class="img-responsive col-xs-12 col-md-10  col-lg-10 " src="img/hill5.jpg" alt="">\n                    </div>\n<p>You can find the rarest endangered species and more than 230 varied species of birds perched on trees or flying around. I was so captured by their beauty that I did not miss this opportunity to capture them in my camera. I would say it''s a bird watcher''s paradise. You can find solitude in these areas and can just ease all your worries in the comfort provided by Mother Nature. You do not have to burn a hole in your pocket to visit this place; all you need is a camera. </p>\n<p>Weekends do not count unless you spend them wholeheartedly by pushing all your worries aside. Hope you have a relaxing weekend because they are the perfect days to refuel your soul.So pack up & leave, don''t wait more. </p>\n\n', 'Geeta Sowmya', 'hill.jpg', 'hillrec.jpg');

